e, this study focuses on the agenda of the various rulers in the Romanian Principalities, the conflicts among the elites and the rising popularity of music theatre. The book thus combines the study of the political, social, cultural and above all musical history of Romania.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMusical theaterxHistoryy20th century. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Opera.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783205204824423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783205204824.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DKUb2016